==English==
===Etymology 1===
Abbreviation of '''M'''om '''I''''d '''L'''ike to '''F'''uck. Popularized by the teen movie ''[[w:American Pie_(film)|American Pie]]'' (1999), although its usage predates the movie.
:''While looking at a picture of Stifler's mom''
:John: Dude that chick's a MILF! 
:Justin: What to hell is that? 
:John: M-I-L-F Mom I'd Like to Fuck! 
:Justin: Yeah dude! Yeah! 

====Pronunciation====
*[[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|IPA]]: /mɪɫf/
*[[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|SAMPA]]: /<tt>mI5f</tt>/

====Noun====
'''MILF'''  (''plural:'' '''[[MILFs]]''') 
#''(acronym)'' {{vulgar}}: A (putative) [[mother]] found sexually attractive.
#:''Tom's mother is hot &mdash; she's a real '''MILF'''.''
=====Usage note=====
''MILF'' has quickly become a much used descriptor on the internet for pornography sites featuring women mostly between the ages of 35 and 50.

===Etymology 2===
Abbreviation of ''[[w:Moro Islamic Liberation Front|Moro Islamic Liberation Front]]''.
====Noun====
'''MILF'''  (''plural:'' '''[[MILFs]]''') 
#''(initialism)'' '''M'''oro '''I'''slamic '''L'''iberation '''F'''ront, an organization in the Philippines seeking to establish an Islamic state on the island of Mindanao. Distinctly different from the [[MNLF]] or Moro National Liberation Front which, though has a similar goal, is composed of different leaders.

